o conceptualize romanticism is to accept its complicated nature and acknowledge that there is no “single basket” to contain it. Gay conceives of romantics in “families,” whose individual members share fundamental values but retain unique qualities. He concludes by demonstrating that romanticism extends well into the twentieth century, where its deep and lasting impact may be measured in the work of writers such as T. S. Eliot and Virginia Woolf.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mrz 2021) 0aRomanticism in art. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300210095423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300210095.jpg  a978-3-11-067250-3  YUP eBook Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles